HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 284
BY REPRESENTATIVE SPELL
A RESOLUTION
To designate Wednesday, May 22, 2026, as World Preeclampsia Awareness Day in
Louisiana.
WHEREAS, May is recognized nationally and internationally as Preeclampsia
Awareness Month and aims to increase understanding of this life-threatening hypertensive
disorder of pregnancy; and
WHEREAS, World Preeclampsia Day is observed annually on May twenty-second
to raise global awareness of preeclampsia, a serious pregnancy-related condition that poses
significant risks to maternal and infant health; and
WHEREAS, preeclampsia is most often characterized by a rapid rise in blood
pressure that can lead to seizure, stroke, multiple organ failure, and the death of the mother
and baby; and
WHEREAS, the United States currently ranks forty-seventh worldwide for maternal
mortality and is the only industrialized nation with a rising maternal mortality rate; and
WHEREAS, in the United States, preeclampsia complicates approximately one in
every twenty-five pregnancies; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana recorded a maternal mortality rate of 41.9 deaths per
one hundred thousand live births, which is the highest rate in the nation; and
WHEREAS, according to America's Health Rankings, 18.3 percent of Louisiana
women between the ages of eighteen and forty-four have been diagnosed with high blood
pressure, placing Louisiana forty-sixth among all states; and
