WHEREAS, sixty percent of hypertension-related maternal deaths are considered
potentially preventable with timely diagnosis, treatment, and coordinated care; and
WHEREAS, maternal death has profound and lasting emotional, social, and
economic impacts on families and communities throughout Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, the primary treatment for preeclampsia involves early delivery of the
infant to prevent disease progression and complications; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana ranked fifty-first among the fifty states and Puerto
Rico for premature births, and preeclampsia is recorded as a significant contributing factor
to such births; and
WHEREAS, Louisiana continues to rank among the states with the highest infant
mortality rates in the United States, with nine deaths per one thousand live births compared
to the national average of 5.6, according to America's Health Rankings; and
WHEREAS, it is imperative that Louisiana address the prevalence of infant and
maternal mortality in the state and work to provide more effective care for the state's
expecting mothers and unborn children.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, May 22, 2026, as World
Preeclampsia Awareness Day in Louisiana and does hereby acknowledge Woman's Hospital
for providing care to pregnant women to help reduce maternal and infant deaths and reduce
the number of pre-term births.
